com.rds_software.customers.menarini.projects.odp.backend.repos.csv

Class CsvOdpFileManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rds_software.customers.menarini.projects.odp.backend.repos.csv.CsvOdpFileManager

  • public class CsvOdpFileManager
extends Object
    File manager for handling CSV file I/O operations in the ODP repository. Provides thread-safe read/write operations with atomic file updates.

    Manages the following CSV files:

    • odps.csv - Main ODP records
    • authorization_flows.csv - Authorization steps (without userRole, uses userId foreign key)
    • companies.csv - Company reference data
    • currencies.csv - Currency reference data
    • suppliers.csv - Supplier reference data
    • account_vds.csv - Account/VDS reference data
    • cdc.csv - CDC (Cost Center) reference data
    • cdr.csv - CDR (Revenue Center) reference data
    • user_companies.csv - User-to-company mappings
    • user_roles.csv - User-to-role mappings (normalized from authorization_flows.csv)

    If any CSV files are missing during initialization, they are automatically copied from the template folder located at template/ relative to this class.

    Author:
    Claude Code

      • appendAuthorizationFlow

        public void appendAuthorizationFlow(List<String> record)
                             throws IOException
        Appends an authorization flow record to the CSV file.

        Note: Authorization flow records store only userId as a foreign key reference to user_roles.csv. The userRole field is not included in authorization_flows.csv to avoid data redundancy.

        Parameters:
        record - the record values to append (should not include userRole)
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs appending to the file
